latestPosts.caption:
With how hectic life gets sometimes, a quick escape is all you really need and @villa_maati did just that for us.
Just 26 km from Bangalore, this spacious, earthy villa gave us the pause we didn’t know we needed.

With 5 thoughtfully done bedrooms, a fully equipped kitchen, a cozy little bar, and quiet corners everywhere - it’s the kind of space that lets you slow down without trying too hard.

We spent our time swimming in the giant pool, walking barefoot on soft grass, and simply soaking in the calm. There’s something about the open sky, the stillness, and the soft sun on stone that makes you feel grounded again.

The food was home-style and delicious, the staff were warm and attentive, and the entire space was spotless which made the whole experience even better.

Whether you want to unwind, spend time with friends, or just disconnect from the noise for a bit, this is such a perfect little getaway within city limits.

Honestly, just a great feeling all around.

@villa_maati @thestoriescollective

latestPosts.caption:
Been a little quiet on here, not for any dramatic reason, just because sometimes a girl needs a break. Life gets busy. I’ve been eating my favourite food, spending time with people who feel like home, working on myself, and tuning into what I need. 

Honestly, Instagram sometimes starts to feel a bit like work, and I need a break from that too. But I’m great and I’ll be using this space to do what I love to do most, just post my life (& a bit of collaborations too - pls guys bare with me -)
